This paper focuses on capsule networks for natural language processing (NLP) applications, which is a subfield of computer science that falls under the category of "Computation and Language" (cs.CL). The paper also introduces an adaptive optimizer, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning and falls under the category of "Machine Learning" (cs.LG). Capsule networks are a type of neural network, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions multi-label text classification, which is a common NLP task that involves predicting multiple labels for a given text, and falls under the category of "Neural and Evolutionary Computing" (cs.NE). Finally, the paper mentions question answering, which is a task that involves understanding natural language and falls under the category of "Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition" (cs.CV).
